INSTALLATION:

   For installation instructions, use your web browser to read the file
   doc/install.html.  That is, open the URL:

        file:<full-path-of-this-directory>/doc/install.html

SUMMARIZED CONTENTS:

   LICENSE                   - GPL license covering this software
   configure		     - configuration script
   Makefile.in		     - top-level Makefile template

   bbs/*                     - sample conference files for testing

   css/abalone/*             - style sheets for abalone interface

   doc/*                     - documentation
   doc/CHANGES		     - revision history
   doc/install*.html         - detailed Backtalk installation instructions
   doc/admin*.html           - detailed administrative manual for Backtalk
   doc/language.html         - Backtalk script language manual
   doc/glossary.html         - extensive Backtalk terminology list

   image/*                   - images
   image/pistacho/*          - buttons for pistachio interface
   image/abalone/*           - buttons for abalone interface

   incl/*                    - header files for backtalk
   incl/config.h.in          - Backtalk configuration file template

   misc/*                    - miscellaneous stuff
   misc/browser_list         - database of web browsers
   misc/newuser.html.in      - template for form for creating accounts
   misc/newacct.html.in      - template for page displayed to new users
   misc/cgitest              - script to test CGI execution on your server

   script/*                  - Backtalk scripts
   script/config.bt.in       - template for Backtalk configuration script
   script/pistachio/*        - Pistachio interface
   script/abalone/*          - Abalone interface
   script/admin/*            - Administrative interface
   sript/welcome             - Default welcome script

   src/*                     - Backtalk source code

   sql/*                     - SQL query sets for various SQL servers

NOTE:
 * mod_auth_external.c and pwauth.c are no longer part of this distribution.
   They have been broken out and are distributed for free at
   http://www.unixpapa.com/mod_auth_external.html

 * The vanilla interface is no longer part of this distribution.  It too is
   now separately distributed.  You can get it, at
   http://www.unixpapa.com/backtalk/download.html
